/-!
# LMFDB level-1 modular form orbit `1.170.a.{a..}` (Hecke field degree 13)

The Hecke field `K = ℚ(α)` is degree 13 over ℚ. The LMFDB lists q-coefficients as
elements of `K`, which we decompose as `c_0 + c_1 · α + … + c_{12} · α^12`.
The combined form is `f = f_0 + α · f_1 + … + α^12 · f_{12}`, with each
`f_j` a level-1 weight-170 form with rational coefficients in `(E₄, E₆)`.

The Sturm bound for weight 170 is `⌊170/12⌋ + 1 = 15`. After certifying agreement
on the first 15 q-coefficients, `ModularForm.eq_of_sturm_bound` lets us conclude that any
form with the same coefficients equals our explicit `lmfdb_1_170_a_orbit`.

Generated by `scripts/lmfdb_qexp_to_e4e6_v3.sage`.
-/

